# Enable generic avoidance framework
# AVOID_ENABLE      1

# Enable ADS-B avoidance logic
# AVD_ENABLE        1

# Enable ADS-B via MAVLink
# ADSB_TYPE         1

AVOID_MARGIN  50
# Avoidance behavior:
# 0 = SLIDE (recommended)
# 1 = STOP
# 2 = GUIDED
#AVOID_BEHAVE      0

# Safety margin (meters)
# AVOID_MARGIN      50

# Optional: make avoidance messages visible
# STATUSTEXT_MASK  0



| Value | Description                                               |
| ----- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| `0`   | **Disable all logging** (no logs are saved)               |
| `1`   | **Log to dataflash** (on-board storage, typically `.bin`) | (default)
| `2`   | **Log to mavlink** (sent to GCS via telemetry)            |
| `3`   | **Both dataflash and mavlink**                            |
| `4`   | **Log to file system** (e.g., when using Linux targets)   |
| `5`   | **Both mavlink and file system**                          |
| `6`   | **Both dataflash and file system**                        |
| `7`   | **Log to all three**: dataflash, mavlink, and file system |
